ll happen. But why did they still make these technologies and keep on creating new platforms? Because technology itself is not harmful. Whether or not the technology is harmful is up to people who use and build technology, like us. User's responsibility is simple, users should do what is morally and ethically right. The best would be all the users being responsible, but 3.6 billion users worldwide are not all responsible. However, engineers can make people responsible because they have control over the technology. This is why professional responsibility is more important than the user's responsibility.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":269},"end":{"line":9,"column":788,"offset":1056}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":269},"end":{"line":9,"column":788,"offset":1056}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Professional Responsibility","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":1062},"end":{"line":11,"column":30,"offset":1089}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":1060},"end":{"line":11,"column":30,"offset":1089}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Recently many social media platforms have worked hard to protect their users from getting hate comments.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":3,"offset":1095},"end":{"line":13,"column":107,"offset":1199}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1093},"end":{"line":13,"column":109,"offset":1201}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1093},"end":{"line":13,"column":109,"offset":1201}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://fossbytes.com/instagram-asks-rethink-hate-comments-restrict-feature/","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"On January 2019, Instagram introduces two features","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":4,"offset":1208},"end":{"line":15,"column":54,"offset":1258}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":2,"offset":1206},"end":{"line":15,"column":56,"offset":1260}}},{"type":"text","value":" (click for more information)","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":56,"offset":1260},"end":{"line":15,"column":85,"offset":1289}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1205},"end":{"line":15,"column":164,"offset":1368}}},{"type":"text","value":".\n","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":164,"offset":1368},"end":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1371}}},{"type":"raw","value":"<br/>","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1371},"end":{"line":16,"column":6,"offset":1376}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":6,"offset":1376},"end":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":1378}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":3,"offset":1380},"end":{"line":17,"column":8,"offset":1385}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":1378},"end":{"line":17,"column":10,"offset":1387}}},{"type":"text","value":" feature is making users rethink before they post. The way this feature works is pretty simple. AI will read the comment after the user clicks post, and if the comment contains words that might offend other users, it will ask the user question like \"Are you sure you want to post this?\". The purpose of asking this question is to make the user rethink the word choice. It is not simply just making the user reconsider, but also let users aware that this comment is not ethically accepted and forces users to not post it.\n","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":10,"offset":1387},"end":{"line":18,"column":1,"off